VersionDetector
===============

Simple rails plugin which extracts the current version out of a git / svn repo and show it on a page.

We use svn to deploy our applications and its always useful to see what release/branch and revision number a application is running.

Usage
=====

1. Install the plugin

$ ./script/plugin install git://github.com/retoo/version_detector.git

2. Add this to your application.haml (What? you dont use haml)?

.version= "V: #{VersionDetector::VERSION}"

3. Add a nice styling to .version

Ideas
=====
 - use git describe for the git version string
 - Only show the verison numer



